parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, premature wear, and potentially cause the engine to seize, resulting in costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle uses more than one quart of oil every 400 miles or less
frequent oil changes
and engine knocking or noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to shift into gear
stuck in one gear
or unable to reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or overheat, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine knocks
makes excessive noise
or has low compression
resulting in stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and axle issues can cause the vehicle to jerk, stall, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
or the axle has a small leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption and Engine Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
requiring frequent oil changes
and may exhibit symptoms such as white smoke from the exhaust
knocking or stalling
and engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as engine stalling
loss of power
and unusual noises from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended engine start can cause accidents or injuries, especially if the vehicle is in gear or if the driver is not prepared to operate the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine starts without the key being in the ignition
or without the driver's intention.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially during inclement weather conditions.
symptoms: Windshield wipers stop working
wipers stick in the up position
wipers do not move
wipers make a loud noise
wipers work intermittently
wipers only work on low speed
wipers do not return to their normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the defroster/heater system can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially during inclement weather conditions.
symptoms: Defroster/heater does not work
defroster/heater blows cold air
defroster/heater makes a popping noise
defroster/heater switches from heat to cold air
defroster/heater does not provide heat to the windshield
defroster/heater affects the illumination of the dash and radio lighting.
